docs.abstract: A House committee sought briefings from search engines whose services might have been leveraged by the site, which has been linked to numerous deaths. Seven House members asked the Justice Department about avenues for investigation.
docs.snippet: A House committee sought briefings from search engines whose services might have been leveraged by the site, which has been linked to numerous deaths. Seven House members asked the Justice Department about avenues for investigation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lawmakers in Washington are prodding technology companies to limit the visibility and reduce the risks of a website that provides detailed instructions about suicide and asking the nation’s top law enforcement official to consider pursuing a Justice Department inquiry.

headline.main: Lawmakers Urge Big Tech to ‘Mitigate Harm’ of Suicide Site and Seek Justice Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Lawmakers Urge Big Tech and Justice Dept. to Act on Suicide Site

keywords.name: organizations
keywords.value: House Committee on Energy and Commerce

byline.original: By Gabriel J.X. Dance and Megan Twohey

docs.abstract: The group was likely using the websites to install malware that helped it gather data from government agencies and other groups, the company said.
docs.snippet: The group was likely using the websites to install malware that helped it gather data from government agencies and other groups, the company said.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft said on Monday that it had seized 42 websites from a Chinese hacking group in an effort to disrupt the group’s intelligence-gathering operations.

headline.main: Microsoft Seizes 42 Websites From a Chinese Hacking Group
headline.print_headline: Group’s Sites Are Seized By Microsoft For Hacking
